<item>
            <title>[SPR-11460] Include GsonHttpMessageConverter in Spring MVC</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-11460</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am working on a number of projects that use GSON for JSON serialization.  However, in the web layer we are using Jackson 2 for similar purposes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It will be good if the class &lt;tt&gt;GsonHttpMessageConverter&lt;/tt&gt; from the Spring Android REST project were to be made available with Spring MVC core as then we would be able to avoid two different libraries in the same project.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other desirable features of GSON are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Single JAR compared to at least 3 Jackson-2 JARs (annotations, core, databind);&lt;br/&gt;
2. Smaller JAR footprint (186K v/s 35K + 194K + 893K);&lt;br/&gt;
3. GSON does not serialize fields with null values, Jackson does (&lt;p/&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;syntaxplugin&quot; class=&quot;syntaxplugin&quot; style=&quot;border: 1px dashed #bbb; border-radius: 5px !important; overflow: auto; max-height: 30em;&quot;&gt;
